[30;1m64 | [0m[35mThis implementation of YAML Path is a *query language* in addition to a *node[0m
[30;1m65 | [0m[35mdescriptor*.  With it, you can describe or select a single precise node or[0m
[30;1m66 | [0m[35msearch for any number of nodes that match some criteria.  Keys, values,[0m
[30;1m67 | [0m[35melements, anchors, and aliases can all be searched at any number of levels[0m
[30;1m68 | [0m[35mwithin the data structure using the same query.  Collectors can also be used to[0m
[30;1m69 | [0m[35mgather and further select from otherwise disparate parts of the source data.[0m
[30;1m70 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m204 | [0m[35m    `/hash[name%admin]/pass[encrypted!^ENC\[]`[0m
[30;1m205 | [0m[35m  * Descendent node searches:[0m
[30;1m206 | [0m[35m    `structure[has.descendant.with=something].has.another.field` or[0m
[30;1m207 | [0m[35m    `/structure[/has/descendant/with=something]/has/another/field`[0m
[30;1m208 | [0m[35m* Array element searches with all of the search methods above via `.` (yields[0m

[30;1m24 | [0m[35m        Matches only the key-name or element-index of the present node,[0m
[30;1m25 | [0m[35m        discarding any and all child node data.  Can be used to rename the[0m
[30;1m26 | [0m[35m        matched key as long as the new name is unique within the parent, lest[0m
